To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Arkansas Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Public records relating to roadway debris or roadway hazards on Interstate 40 westbound near Exit 280 in Arkansas. This request includes records maintained by your organization's headquarters, district offices, divisions, contractors, and any other personnel or systems reasonably likely to contain responsive records. The time period for this request is May 1, 2025 through June 3, 2025. Specifically, I request the following categories of records:

1. Roadway Inspection and Patrol Records
a) All roadway inspection reports for Interstate 40 near Exit 280;
b) Interstate patrol logs or roadway patrol activity logs;
c) Maintenance patrol schedules or dispatch records;
d) Any records reflecting when your organization's personnel inspected, patrolled, or otherwise visited the roadway in this area.

2. Debris Removal and Maintenance Records
a) Debris removal logs or cleanup reports;
b) Maintenance work orders, service tickets, or complaints relating to debris removal;
c) Maintenance management system records relating to roadway hazards;
d) Records of maintenance activities performed near the specified location.

3. Hazard Reports and Complaints
a) Records of reports from motorists regarding roadway debris or hazards;
b) Complaint logs referencing debris on Interstate 40 near Exit 280;
c) Records of calls, emails, or electronic submissions reporting roadway debris.

4. Communications and Incident Records
a) Internal emails, memoranda, or communications referencing roadway debris near Exit 280;
b) Communications between your organization and other organizations, contractors, agencies, or entities regarding debris at or near this location;
c) Communications between your organization's personnel discussing roadway hazards on Interstate 40 near Exit 280.

5. Photographs, Video, and Other Media
a) Photographs of roadway debris or hazards at the specified location;
b) Video recordings taken by your organization's personnel relating to roadway conditions near Exit 280;
c) Any other visual documentation relating to debris removal or roadway hazards.

6. Post-Incident Records
a) Records reflecting any investigation conducted by your organization regarding roadway debris at this location following June 2, 2025;
b) Records reflecting corrective actions taken following any debris incident at the specified location.

7. Databases and Electronic Records
If responsive records are maintained in electronic databases or maintenance management systems, I request electronic exports or reports reflecting responsive data fields.

This request includes records maintained in any format, including paper records, electronic files, databases, email systems, and archived storage systems.

If any portion of the requested records is withheld under a claimed exemption, please provide:
a) The statutory basis for the exemption; and
b) All reasonably segregable non-exempt portions of the records.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Alexander Dua
